rows.name: Athletic
rows.description: Whether at gyms, courts, or rinks or in pools these active sports programs and events will get your heart rate and your competitive spirit up.

rows.name: Cultural
rows.description: Be musical; be artistic; be dramatic! Dance, draw, or drum your way to fun with programs designed to inspire.

rows.name: School Year
rows.description: Children can make friends, get homework help, be active, and learn arts and crafts at these activities that are scheduled around the school day.

rows.name: Educational & Mentoring
rows.description: From cooking and computers to book clubs and resume building, young and old can grow and learn with these activities.

rows.name: Fitness
rows.description: Get into shape with yoga, aerobics, and other exercise programs for all ages and experience levels.

rows.name: Games
rows.description: Have fun indoors playing table tennis, video games, chess and other board games with your friends, families, and neighbors.

rows.name: Summer Camps
rows.description: Affordable, fun and safe summer programming for children of all ages in neighborhoods throughout the city! Neighborhood camps offer arts & crafts, sports, and trips. Citywide specialty camps focus on arts, sports, and the environment.

rows.name: Civic & Community
rows.description: Engage your neighbors through volunteer opportunities and community meetings on important topics that matter to your neighborhood.

rows.name: Environmental
rows.description: Our knowledgeable staff are here to help you learn what's in your backyard and its ecosystem.

rows.name: Programs for People with Disabilities
rows.description: Programs that support the mental, physical, social, cultural, and emotional growth of people with disabilities.
